  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf a builder is configured for the beacon node but it is unavailable at startup then prysm shuts down.  Other beacon nodes note that the builder is unavailable and continue with local execution payloads (they also appear to check periodically if the builder is back up, and allow blinded block production if so).\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nRun the beacon node with `--builder=http://localhost:18550` but without anything listening on that port.\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\n{\"level\":\"error\",\"msg\":\"could not connect to builder: Get \\\"http://localhost:18550/eth/v1/builder/status\\\": dial tcp [::1]:18550: connect: connection refused\",\"prefix\":\"main\",\"time\":\"2022-08-31T20:40:56Z\"}\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\nPrysm 3.0.0",
